1063  	 	SHORT-LIVED 6d "VIA NEW YORK" RATE COVER WITH IRELAND ISLAND "3" NUMERAL; 8 Jan. 1878 env. (part flap lost) to Bristol "Via New York" unusually franked by a Pair of 3d Yellows just tied by a single fine Ireland Island "3" barred numeral with a mostly fine matching large double-arc "IRELAND ISLE/BERMUDA" PM5 c.d.s. (first used in 1845!) alongside. This 6d rate via the US lasted for less than two years (23 May 1877 to 31 Mar. 1879); examples are very hard to find. PHOTO.  	£240
</p>
