1064  	 	SHORT-LIVED 6d "VIA NEW YORK" RATE - TRIPLE RATE COVER TO G.B. WITH ST. GEORGES "B/1" NUMERAL; Long 8 Aug. 1878 "O.H.M.S." env. (flap lost; ends folded in slightly) to London "Via New York" franked for the 1oz+ 1s-6d rate (in force on the US route for less than 2 years) by 1/- Green + 6d Dull Lilac tied by poor (as so often) tall barred K2 St. Georges "B/1" numerals with mostly fine matching oval "ST. GEORGES/BERMUDA" d.s. on the front. PHOTO.  	£200
