<p style="font-size:smaller">
1065  	 	EARLY U.P.U. RATE - 4d-RATE COVER TO G.B. "VIA HALIFAX, N.S." WITH 2d + 1d PAIR FRANKING; 8 Nov. 1879 env. (part flap lost) to London "Via Halifax, N.S." franked for the new (as of 1st April 1879) UPU 4d rate with 2d Blue (clear profile) and 1d Pir tied by v. fine (at left) and partial (as per regulations - the duplex was only supposed to be struck once on multi-franked covers at this date) strikes of the new (as of 1879) "HAMILTON/BERMUDA/1" Duplex (code "C"). The first 4d value was not available until March 1880, so the new UPU rate had to be prepaid with 1d/2d values at this time. PHOTO.  	£140
</p>
