<p style="font-size:smaller">
1066  	 	"INLAND-ISLAND/BERMUDA/3" ERROR OF SPELLING DUPLEX ON 6d-RATE COVER TOP G.B.; 18/21 Jan. 1880 env. (with original contents headed "HMS Northampton, Bermuda"; from a Midshipman with sketch of newly painted ship's colour-scheme, and news of a gunnery accident with exploding shells) to Hampshire franked by 2d Blue & Pair of 1d Reds (one with fault at top) tied by partly very fine "INLAND-ISLAND/B[ERMUDA]/3" duplexes showing the "INLAND" for "IRELAND" Error (in use 1879-89 and very elusive). Fine example of this popular (and unusual) Duplex Spelling Error. PHOTO.  	£300
</p>
</div>


<div style="width:98%;margin:0 auto">
