<p style="font-size:smaller">
1067  	 	THE RARE EARLY ST. GEORGES "REGISTERED" STRAIGHT-LINE MARK; Attractive 2 Mar. 1881 front of an envelope to Southampton endorsed "Registered" and "Pr. HMS Alpha via Halifax" franked by a 6d Dull Lilac tied by a very fine "ST. GEORGES/BERMUDA/2" Duplex matching the very fine large black "REGISTERED" mark alongside. Only a handful of this Registered mark have been recorded; early Bermudan Registered Mail is rare. PHOTO.  	£150
</p>
