1069  	 	ST. GEORGES - MATCHED TRIO AT SINGLE, DOUBLE & TRIPLE U.P.U. 
RATES TO G.B. INC. BLUE DUPLEX, ETC.; 
Unusual set of three covers - 1 Mar. 1883, 11 Sept. 1884 & 4 Dec. 1884 - 
from the same correspondence to London franked for the 1/- (triple), 
4d (single) and 8d (double) UPU rates respectively; franked by a 
single 1/- Green tied by a mostly very fine scarce BLUE "B"-code Duplex, 
by a 2d Blue Pair tied by "A"-code Duplex and by a 3d Orange with 21⁄2d Blues 
(2) tied by mostly fine "B"-code Duplexes. The Blue Duplex has only been recorded for 31⁄2 years (Dec. 1879 to Apr. 1883). Remarkable matched 
set of the 3 rates from one correspondence. (3 covers) PHOTO.  	£300
</p>
