1070  	 	HAMILTON - MATCHED PAIR OF THE FIRST DUPLEX (TYPES I & II) ON 4d-RATE COVERS TO G.B.; 7 May 1885 & 1 Mar. 1888 pair of envs. (latter with creasing on reverse) from the D'Esterre Correspondence to Plymouth each franked by a 4d Orange-Red tied by a very fine "B"-code "HAMILTON/BERMUDA/1" Duplex; the first being the normal Type I (recorded 1879-87), the second being the rare short-lived Type II (1888 only). Good pair. (2 covers) PHOTO.  	£150
