1071  	 	ST. GEORGES - RARE 3-COLOUR FRANKING (1d + 1⁄2d + 21⁄2d) ON 4d-RATE COVER TO G.B.; Unusual 13 Jan. 1887 env. (slight stains barely detract) to London franked for the U.P.U. 4d rate with 1d Rose, 1⁄2d Stone & 21⁄2d Ultramarine (some perfs. of the stamps rubbed along top) tied by mostly very fine "ST. GEORGES/A/BERMUDA/2" Duplexes. A most unusual and seemingly commercial franking for the 4d rate. PHOTO.  	£260
