1072  	 	EARLY REGISTERED MAIL - HAMILTON "R" IN OVAL MARK ON 6d-RATE COVER TO G.B.; 16 Nov. 1887 env. registered to Birmingham franked by a 6d Dull Mauve (cut wing margin at left) tied by a very fine "B"-code "HAMILTON/BERMUDA/1" Type I Duplex with a matching superb Hamilton "R" in oval on the front. This "R" mark is recorded from 1884 to 1906 but early strikes as fine as this are very elusive. PHOTO.  	£150
</p>
