1073  	 	EARLY REGISTERED MAIL - RARE IRELAND ISLAND "R" IN OVAL ON 6d-RATE COVER TO G.B.; Fine 3 Mar. 1889 env. (printed "H.M.S. BUZZARD" flap) "Registered" to Manchester franked by a 6d Dull Mauve tied by a mostly fine correctly spelled "IRELAND ISLAND/A/BERMUDA/3" Duplex matching the very fine (curiously double-framed) "R" in Oval mark in the opposite corner. This "R" mark of Ireland Island is very rare; Proud only records a single date (7 July 1898) though it was issued in 1883. Exhibition Quality. PHOTO.  	£240
</p>
