1074  	 	THE VERY RARE 2d SAILOR's CONCESSION RATE COVER TO G.B. VIA THE U.S. (1d FOR THE U.S. + 1d FOR BERMUDA); Fine 24 Apr. 1889 env. (very slight edge wear) to Sheffield, headed & countersigned for the Concession Rate for a "Seaman, H.M.S. Bellerophon, Bermuda" with the handstruck signature- mark of the "Commanding Officer", franked by a Bermuda 2d Blue tied by a light "IRELAND ISLAND/B/BERMUDA/3" Duplex with a Sheffield (9 May) backstamp. This 2d rate was for mails sent via the New York route to enable the US to claim half the postage; examples from Bermuda are extremely rare. [The similar but stained 1880 Soldier's cover in the Sattin 2004 auction realised £2,930.] Important Exhibition Item. PHOTO.  	£2000
</p>
