1077  	 	LATE FEE MAIL - ST. GEORGES & HAMILTON SUPPLEMENTARY MAIL DOUBLE-POSTAGE RATE COVERS VIA/TO THE U.S.; Fine 17 Sept. 1891 commercial env. to London endorsed "via N[ew]. Y[ork]." franked by two 4d Orange Reds (overlapped) tied by two mostly fine "ST. GEORGES/A/BERMUDA/2" Duplexes, apparently carried on the last-minute connection to catch the outbound steamer 21⁄2 hours after the normal mails had gone. Plus similar 25 July 1903 env. to New York with 21⁄2d Ultramarine vertical pair tied by a single v. fine double-circle "HAMILTON/BERMUDA" c.d.s. also apparently paid double to catch the SS Pretoria 3 hours after she had left. Rare pair. (2 covers) PHOTO.  	£150
